- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper mentions the use of cameras for mapping and localization, indicating a computer vision component. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, but it is possible that some of the methods used for point cloud registration and visual feature matching involve machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Similar to cs.LG, the paper does not explicitly mention AI, but it is possible that some of the methods used for mapping and localization involve AI techniques. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This category is less likely, but the paper does mention the use of visual feature matching, which could involve natural language processing techniques for text-based feature matching.
